    "The difference between DenseGNN-KNN and DenseGNN-Voronoi lies in the edge selection method, with the former using a KNNs approach and the latter a Voronoi-based approach.",
    "Den-seGNN-Lite, as shown in Fig.",
    "S1, is a streamlined version of DenseGNN that maintains performance while substantially reducing the number of training parameters.",
    "Evaluation on the QM9 molecular property dataset (130,829 molecules) showed that DenseGNN achieved competitive results on multiple tasks compared to other reference models, such as SchNet, MEGNet, enn-s2s 45, ALIGNN, and DimeNet++ 46, especially in tasks like Highest Occupied Molecular Orbital (HOMO) and energy gap (Δϵ), as shown in Fig. 5.",
    "DenseGNN outperformed ALIGNN in most tasks and approached the performance of DimeNet++."
